#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Barbarian\n"
"## The Barbarian\n"
"| Level | Proficiency Bonus | Rages     | Rage Damage | Features                                      "
"|\n"
"|-------|-------------------|-----------|-------------|-----------------------------------------------|\n"
"| 1st   | +2                | 2         | +2          | Rage, Unarmored "
"Defense                       |\n"
"| 2nd   | +2                | 2         | +2          | Reckless Attack, "
"Danger Sense                 |\n"
"| 3rd   | +2                | 3         | +2          | Primal Path                                   "
"|\n"
"| 4th   | +2                | 3         | +2          | Ability Score "
"Improvement                     |\n"
"| 5th   | +3                | 3         | +2          | Extra Attack, Fast "
"Movement                   |\n"
"| 6th   | +3                | 4         | +2          | Path feature                                  "
"|\n"
"| 7th   | +3                | 4         | +2          | Feral Instinct                                "
"|\n"
"| 8th   | +3                | 4         | +2          | Ability Score "
"Improvement                     |\n"
"| 9th   | +4                | 4         | +3          | Brutal Critical (1 "
"die)                       |\n"
"| 10th  | +4                | 4         | +3          | Path feature                                  "
"|\n"
"| 11th  | +4                | 4         | +3          | Relentless                                    "
"|\n"
"| 12th  | +4                | 5         | +3          | Ability Score "
"Improvement                     |\n"
"| 13th  | +5                | 5         | +3          | Brutal Critical (2 "
"dice)                      |\n"
"| 14th  | +5                | 5         | +3          | Path Feature                                  "
"|\n"
"| 15th  | +5                | 5         | +3          | Persistent Rage                               "
"|\n"
"| 16th  | +5                | 5         | +4          | Ability Score "
"Improvement                     |\n"
"| 17th  | +6                | 6         | +4          | Brutal Critical (3 "
"dice)                      |\n"
"| 18th  | +6                | 6         | +4          | Indomitable Might                             "
"|\n"
"| 19th  | +6                | 6         | +4          | Ability Score "
"Improvement                     |\n"
"| 20th  | +6                | Unlimited | +4          | Primal Champion                               "
"|\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:28
msgid "## Class Features As a barbarian, you gain the following class features."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:33
msgid ""
"### Hit Points **Hit Dice:** 1d12 per barbarian level **Hit Points at 1st "
"Level:** 12 + your Constitution modifier **Hit Points at Higher Levels:** "
"1d12 (or 7) + your Constitution modifier per barbarian level after 1st"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Proficiencies\n"
"**Armor:** Light armor, medium armor, shields   \n"
"**Weapons:** Simple weapons, martial weapons   \n"
"**Tools:** None   \n"
"**Saving Throws:** Strength, Constitution   \n"
"**Skills:** Choose two from Animal Handling, Athletics, Intimidation, "
"Nature, Perception, and Survival   \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:43
msgid ""
"### Equipment You start with the following equipment, in addition to the "
"equipment granted by your background:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:47
msgid "(a) a greataxe or (b) any martial melee weapon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:47
msgid "(a) two handaxes or (b) any simple weapon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:47
msgid "An explorer's pack and four javelins"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Rage \n"
"- - -\n"
"In battle, you fight with primal ferocity. On your turn, you can enter a "
"rage as a bonus action.   \n"
"While raging, you gain the following benefits if you aren't wearing heavy "
"armor:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:56
msgid "You have advantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:56
msgid ""
"When you make a melee weapon attack using Strength, you gain a bonus to the "
"damage roll that increases as you gain levels as a barbarian, as shown in "
"the Rage Damage column of the Barbarian table."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:56
msgid "You have resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:60
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are able to cast spells, you can't cast them or concentrate on them "
"while raging.   \n"
"Your rage lasts for 1 minute. It ends early if you are knocked unconscious "
"or if your turn ends and you haven't attacked a hostile creature since your "
"last turn or taken damage since then. You can also end your rage on your "
"turn as a bonus action.   \n"
"Once you have raged the number of times shown for your barbarian level in "
"the Rages column of the Barbarian table, you must finish a long rest before "
"you can rage again. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:64
msgid ""
"### Unarmored Defense - - - While you are not wearing any armor, your Armor "
"Class equals 10 + your Dexterity modifier + your Constitution modifier. You "
"can use a shield and still gain this benefit."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:68
msgid ""
"### Reckless Attack - - - Starting at 2nd level, you can throw aside all "
"concern for defense to attack with fierce desperation. When you make your "
"first attack on your turn, you can decide to attack recklessly. Doing so "
"gives you advantage on melee weapon attack rolls using Strength during this "
"turn, but attack rolls against you have advantage until your next turn."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:73
msgid ""
"### Danger Sense - - - At 2nd level, you gain an uncanny sense of when "
"things nearby aren't as they should be, giving you an edge when you dodge "
"away from danger.  You have advantage on Dexterity saving throws against "
"effects that you can see, such as traps and spells. To gain this benefit, "
"you can’t be blinded, deafened, or incapacitated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:77
msgid ""
"### Primal Path - - - At 3rd level, you choose a path that shapes the nature "
"of your rage. Choose the Path of the Berserker or the Path of the Totem "
"Warrior, both detailed at the end of the class description. Your choice "
"grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th, 10th, and 14th levels."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:81
msgid ""
"### Ability Score Improvement - - - When you reach 4th level, and again at "
"8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your "
"choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As "
"normal, you can’t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:85
msgid ""
"### Extra Attack - - - Beginning at 5th level, you can attack twice, instead "
"of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:89
msgid ""
"### Fast Movement - - - Starting at 5th level, your speed increases by 10 "
"feet while you aren’t wearing heavy armor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:94
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Feral Instinct \n"
"- - -\n"
"By 7th level, your instincts are so honed that you have advantage on "
"initiative rolls.   \n"
"Additionally, if you are surprised at the beginning of combat and aren't "
"incapacitated, you can act normally on your first turn, but only if you "
"enter your rage before doing anything else on that turn. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:99
msgid ""
"### Brutal Critical - - - Beginning at 9th level, you can roll one "
"additional weapon damage die when determining the extra damage for a "
"critical hit with a melee attack.  This increases to two additional dice at "
"13th level and three additional dice at 17th level."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:104
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Relentless Rage \n"
"- - -\n"
"Starting at 11th level, your rage can keep you fighting despite grievous "
"wounds. If you drop to 0 hit points while you're raging and don't die "
"outright, you can make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw. If you succeed, "
"you drop to 1 hit point instead.   \n"
"Each time you use this feature after the first, the DC increases by 5. When "
"you finish a short or long rest, the DC resets to 10. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:108
msgid ""
"### Persistent Rage - - - Beginning at 15th level, your rage is so fierce "
"that it ends early only if you fall unconscious or if you choose to end it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:112
msgid ""
"### Indomitable Might - - - Beginning at 18th level, if your total for a "
"Strength check is less than your Strength score, you can use that score in "
"place of the total."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:116
msgid ""
"### Primal Champion - - - At 20th level, you embody the power of the "
"wilds. Your Strength and Constitution scores increase by 4. Your maximum for "
"those scores is now 24."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:120
msgid ""
"## Path of the Berserker - - - For some barbarians, rage is a means to an "
"end, that end being violence. The Path of the Berserker is a path of "
"untrammeled fury, slick with blood. As you enter the berserker's rage, you "
"thrill in the chaos of battle, heedless of your own health or well-being."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:123
msgid ""
"#### Frenzy Starting when you choose this path at 3rd level, you can go into "
"a frenzy when you rage. If you do so, for the duration of your rage you can "
"make a single melee weapon attack as a bonus action on each of your turns "
"after this one. When your rage ends, you suffer one level of exhaustion (as "
"described in appendix A)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:126
msgid ""
"#### Mindless Rage Beginning at 6th level, you can't be charmed or "
"frightened while raging. If you are charmed or frightened when you enter "
"your rage, the effect is suspended for the duration of the rage."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:130
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#### Intimidating Presence \n"
"Beginning at 10th level, you can use your action to frighten someone with "
"your menacing presence. When you do so, choose one creature that you can see "
"within 30 feet of you. If the creature can see or hear you, it must succeed "
"on a Wisdom saving throw (**DC equal to 8 + your proficiency bonus + your "
"Charisma modifier**) or be frightened of you until the end of your next "
"turn. On subsequent turns, you can use your action to extend the duration of "
"this effect on the frightened creature until the end of your next turn. This "
"effect ends if the creature ends its turn out of line of sight or more than "
"60 feet away from you.     \n"
"If the creature succeeds on its saving throw, you can't use this feature on "
"that creature again for 24 hours. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/character/classes/barbarian.md:132
msgid ""
"#### Retaliation Starting at 14th level, when you take damage from a "
"creature that is within 5 feet of you, you can use your reaction to make a "
"melee weapon attack against that creature."
msgstr ""
